      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARK THINKER (4) proven at the trip and back in grade for this. Sat on the fast tempo with a tiring fourth over 1400m at Orange in record time. Will relish the claim again from the good gate and her lone victory came over the 1700m. Well placed. BURNING AMBITION (7) Hawkesbury-trained gelding bursting to get off the mark. Kept finding with the 58.5kg for a narrow second over 1720m at Grafton. Well placed with the weight drop and shapes as the main danger. THE BENTLEY (3) has been racing well on the Picnic circuit and gives every indication of running a strong 1700m. Finished runner-up again with a tough second over 1600m at Bourke in the Picnic Cup. Capable of taking a hand in the finish. MAJESTIC ROCA (6) ten-start Maiden gelding who comes out of a Super Maiden with a battling fourth over 1600m at Orange. Finds a suitable assignment this time fourth-up.",
